      "name": "Story Chapter Intro",
      "settings": {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "section_tag": "Where It Began",
        "headline_normal": "They say when you lose someone you love, you spend the rest of your life",
        "headline_italic": "looking for ways to keep talking to them.",
        "para_1": "For me, that conversation happens every time we harvest a flower on our farm.",
        "para_2": "My father, Abhay Manik Birla, didn't just see saffron as a business. He saw it as a legacy of purity. He had a vision of taking the soul of that flower and infusing it into something that could touch people's lives every single morning.",
        "para_3": "He dreamed of a soap that didn't just 'smell' like a memory — but actually carried the living benefit of the saffron he loved so much.",
        "para_closing_italic": "In 2023, when he passed away, that dream became my inheritance."
      }
    },
    "senfa_story_cta_fLQ8GE": {
      "type": "senfa-story-cta",
      "name": "Story Quote",
      "settings": {
        "quote_text": "I realized that if I was going to do this, it couldn't be 'just another soap.' It had to be a <em>standard of integrity</em> that my father would be proud of.",
        "attribution": "— The Founder, Senfa",
        "attribution_sub": "Pune, Maharashtra · Est. 2023"
      }
    },
    "senfa_story_blocks_dtTaUD": {
      "type": "senfa-story-blocks",
      "name": "Story Blocks",
      "settings": {
        "b1_tag": "The Inheritance",
        "b1_heading": "A weight that no business plan",
        "b1_heading_em": "could describe.",
        "b1_para1": "I remember sitting in my office, looking at the saffron threads from our own soil. There was grief. There was love. And there was a question I couldn't shake — what do you do with a dream that isn't yours yet?",
        "b1_pull": "\"If I was going to do this, it couldn't be 'just another soap.' It had to be a standard of integrity that my father would be proud of.\"",
        "b1_para2": "I realised that the saffron in our fields wasn't just a raw material. It was a promise he had already made to every person who would one day hold a bar of Senfa in their hands.",
        "b2_tag": "The Family Mission",
        "b2_heading_em": "I couldn't do it alone.",
        "b2_heading": "And I didn't have to.",
        "b2_para1": "I brought my wife into the heart of the formulation. We sat with my Mama, discussing how to make it as pure as the earth it came from. There were late nights. There were disagreements. There was love holding all of it together.",
        "b2_para2": "And when my cousin Pratik finished his studies, he didn't just join a company. He joined a family mission to protect a name — the name of a man we all loved and wanted to honour.",
        "b2_pull": "\"He didn't join a company. He joined a family mission to protect a name.\"",
        "b3_image": "shopify://shop_images/senfa-soap.jpg",
        "b3_tag": "The Standard",
        "b3_heading": "Months of obsession.",
        "b3_heading_em": "Zero shortcuts.",
        "b3_para1": "We spent months obsessing over the Senfa standard. We refused the shortcuts that make manufacturing easy but make the product hollow.",
        "b3_para2": "We wanted a lather so creamy and an infusion so deep that you could feel the honesty in the water.",
        "b3_pull": "\"We refused the shortcuts that make manufacturing easy but make the product hollow.\"",
        "b3_para3": "If a batch didn't meet the standard — every letter of S-E-N-F-A — it never left our doors. Not once. Not ever."
      }
    },
